{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863982673,"sessionID":"ses_286429a63ffemovC7eb4MkAGfC","part":{"id":"prt_d79bde5ba0016t5MPN42BPpefd","messageID":"msg_d79bdd9ca0010H96eUj35DkBhK","sessionID":"ses_286429a63ffemovC7eb4MkAGfC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_6d88876e95b846d2aa63775d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Command\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-023\n4: - **Module**: cmd/cli\n5: - **Language**: Python\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: The `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to deployed agents via the AgentCube Router or standard Kubernetes Service. The `status` command retrieves and displays the current status of deployed agents. Both commands work with either the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) or the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + Service).\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Package Structure\n16: \n17: ```\n18: cmd/cli/\n19: ├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies\n20: ├── agentcube/\n21: │   ├── __init__.py                             # Package version __version__, exports\n22: │   ├── cli/\n23: │   │   ├── __init__.py                         # CLI subpackage marker\n24: │   │   └── main.py                             # Typer app, invoke/status commands\n25: │   ├── runtime/\n26: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py                  # InvokeRuntime\n27: │   │   └── status_runtime.py                  # StatusRuntime\n28: │   └── services/\n29: │       ├── metadata_service.py                # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n30: │       ├── k8s_provider.py                    # KubernetesProvider\n31: │       └── agentcube_provider.py               # AgentCubeProvider\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ### 1.3 Provider Types\n35: \n36: | Provider | Invocation Target | Status Target |\n37: |----------|-------------------|---------------|\n38: | `agentcube` | AgentRuntime CR via Router | AgentRuntime CR |\n39: | `k8s` | Kubernetes Service | Kubernetes Deployment |\n40: \n41: ## 2. Command Specifications\n42: \n43: ### 2.1 invoke Command\n44: \n45: The `invoke` command POSTs JSON payloads to deployed agents.\n46: \n47: ```python\n48: def invoke(\n49:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n50:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n51:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n52:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n53:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n54: ) -> None:\n55: ```\n56: \n57: **Default Options:**\n58: \n59: | Option | Default |\n60: |--------|---------|\n61: | workspace | \".\" |\n62: | payload | \"{}\" |\n63: | header_list | None |\n64: | provider | \"agentcube\" |\n65: | verbose | False |\n66: \n67: ### 2.2 status Command\n68: \n69: The `status` command retrieves and displays agent deployment status.\n70: \n71: ```python\n72: def status(\n73:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n74:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n75:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n76: ) -> None:\n77: ```\n78: \n79: **Default Options:**\n80: \n81: | Option | Default |\n82: |--------|---------|\n83: | workspace | \".\" |\n84: | provider | \"agentcube\" |\n85: | verbose | False |\n86: \n87: ## 3. Runtime Specifications\n88: \n89: ### 3.1 InvokeRuntime\n90: \n91: Handles agent invocation via HTTP with support for both AgentCube and K8s providers.\n92: \n93: ```python\n94: class InvokeRuntime:\n95:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n96:     \n97:     def invoke(\n98:         self, \n99:         workspace_path: Path, \n100:         payload: Dict[str, Any], \n101:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n102:     ) -> Any: ...\n103:     \n104:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n105:     \n106:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n107:         self, \n108:         agent_id: str, \n109:         payload: Dict[str, Any], \n110:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], \n111:         endpoint: str, \n112:         workspace_path: Path\n113:     ) -> Any: ...\n114:     \n115:     async def _direct_http_invocation(\n116:         self, \n117:         endpoint: str, \n118:         payload: Dict[str, Any], \n119:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], \n120:         workspace_path: Path\n121:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n122: ```\n123: \n124: **Invoke Flow:**\n125: \n126: ```\n127: invoke command (provider=agentcube)\n128:     └─> InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n129:             ├─> _validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n130:             │       └─> Returns: endpoint, namespace, agent_name\n131:             └─> _invoke_agent_via_agentcube()\n132:                     └─> POST to router with session header\n133: \n134: invoke command (provider=k8s)\n135:     └─> InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n136:             └─> _direct_http_invocation()\n137:                     └─> POST to k8s service URL\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Known Issue**: `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` may raise `UnboundLocalError` if `endpoint` doesn't start with `http`.\n141: \n142: ### 3.2 StatusRuntime\n143: \n144: Retrieves and displays agent deployment status.\n145: \n146: ```python\n147: class StatusRuntime:\n148:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n149:     \n150:     def get_status(\n151:         self, \n152:         workspace_path: Path, \n153:         provider: Optional[str] = None\n154:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n155:     \n156:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n157:     \n158:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Status Flow:**\n162: \n163: ```\n164: status command (provider=agentcube)\n165:     └─> StatusRuntime.get_status()\n166:             └─> _get_cr_k8s_status()\n167:                     └─> Query AgentRuntime CR\n168: \n169: status command (provider=k8s)\n170:     └─> StatusRuntime.get_status()\n171:             └─> _get_k8s_status()\n172:                     └─> Query Deployment/Service\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ## 4. Input Validation\n176: \n177: ### 4.1 Workspace Validation\n178: \n179: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n180: |----------|-----------|--------|\n181: | AR-023-004-A | Workspace path does not exist | Raise `FileNotFoundError` |\n182: | AR-023-004-B | Metadata file not found | Raise `FileNotFoundError` |\n183: | AR-023-004-C | Agent not published (no agent_id) | Print warning, exit code 1 |\n184: \n185: ### 4.2 Payload Parsing\n186: \n187: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n188: |----------|-----------|--------|\n189: | AR-023-002-A | Valid JSON | Convert to Python dict |\n190: | AR-023-002-B | Invalid JSON | Print error, exit code 1 |\n191: | AR-023-002-C | Default \"{}\" | Use empty dict |\n192: \n193: ### 4.3 Header Parsing\n194: \n195: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n196: |----------|-----------|--------|\n197: | AR-023-003-A | Single valid header | Add to request headers |\n198: | AR-023-003-B | Multiple headers | Merge all headers |\n199: | AR-023-003-C | Invalid format (no colon) | Print error, exit code 1 |\n200: | AR-023-003-D | Multiple colons | Split on first colon only |\n201: \n202: ## 5. Provider Integration\n203: \n204: ### 5.1 AgentCube Provider (invoke)\n205: \n206: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n207: |----------|-----------|--------|\n208: | AR-023-005-A | Has agent_endpoint | Use endpoint from metadata |\n209: | AR-023-005-B | Has session_id | Add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header |\n210: | AR-023-005-C | k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\" | Rewrite URL to invocations path |\n211: | AR-023-005-D | Missing router_url | Raise `ValueError` |\n212: \n213: **URL Rewrite Logic:**\n214: ```python\n215: if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n216:     base = metadata.agent_endpoint\n217:     endpoint = f\"{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### 5.2 K8s Provider (invoke)\n221: \n222: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n223: |----------|-----------|--------|\n224: | AR-023-006-A | Has k8s_deployment.service_url | Use service URL as endpoint |\n225: | AR-023-006-B | Missing service_url | Raise `ValueError` |\n226: \n227: ### 5.3 AgentCube Provider (status)\n228: \n229: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n230: |----------|-----------|--------|\n231: | AR-023-011-A | CR exists with status | Read status.agentEndpoint |\n232: | AR-023-011-B | CR exists without status | Return \"created_no_status\" |\n233: | AR-023-011-C | CR not found | Return \"not_found_in_k8s\" |\n234: \n235: ### 5.4 K8s Provider (status)\n236: \n237: | Scenario | Condition | Action |\n238: |----------|-----------|--------|\n239: | AR-023-012-A | Deployment exists | Return deployment status |\n240: | AR-023-012-B | Deployment not found | Return \"not_found\" |\n241: \n242: ## 6. HTTP Request/Response\n243: \n244: ### 6.1 Request\n245: \n246: - **Method**: POST\n247: - **Content-Type**: application/json\n248: - **Headers**: \n249:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n250:   - `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: {session_id}` (if available)\n251:   - Custom headers from `--header` option\n252: \n253: ### 6.2 Response Handling\n254: \n255: | Scenario | Response | Action |\n256: |----------|----------|--------|\n257: | AR-023-007-B | Success (2xx) | Print response body |\n258: | AR-023-007-C | Error (4xx/5xx) | Print error in red, exit code 1 |\n259: \n260: ## 7. Output Display\n261: \n262: ### 7.1 Status Table (Rich)\n263: \n264: | Column | Fields |\n265: |--------|--------|\n266: | Field | Agent Name, Provider, Status, Endpoint/Service URL |\n267: | Value | Respective values from metadata and K8s/CR status |\n268: \n269: ### 7.2 Exit Codes\n270: \n271: | Condition | Exit Code |\n272: |-----------|-----------|\n273: | Success | 0 |\n274: | Not published | 1 |\n275: | HTTP error | 1 |\n276: | Invalid payload/header | 1 |\n277: | Exception with verbose | 1 |\n278: \n279: ## 8. Error Handling\n280: \n281: ### 8.1 Error Handling Pattern\n282: \n283: ```python\n284: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n285:     \"\"\"Print error message and optionally full traceback.\"\"\"\n286:     print(f\"Error {command_name}: {e}\", fg=\"red\")\n287:     if verbose:\n288:         traceback.print_exc()\n289:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n290: ```\n291: \n292: ### 8.2 Verbose Mode\n293: \n294: - **Given**: `--verbose` flag is enabled\n295: - **When**: An error occurs\n296: - **Then**: Print full traceback along with error message\n297: \n298: ## 9. Acceptance Criteria\n299: \n300: - [ ] AC001: Invoke command accepts all specified CLI options (workspace, payload, header, provider, verbose)\n301: - [ ] AC002: Invoke validates JSON payload and exits with code 1 for invalid JSON\n302: - [ ] AC003: Invoke validates header format and exits with code 1 for invalid headers\n303: - [ ] AC004: Invoke adds session header (X-Agentcube-Session-Id) when session_id exists in metadata\n304: - [ ] AC005: Invoke validates agent is published before attempting to invoke\n305: - [ ] AC006: Invoke rewrites URL for AgentRuntime CR deployments\n306: - [ ] AC007: Invoke sends POST request with JSON body and appropriate headers\n307: - [ ] AC008: Status command accepts all specified CLI options (workspace, provider, verbose)\n308: - [ ] AC009: Status validates workspace and metadata exist before proceeding\n309: - [ ] AC010: Status returns \"not_published\" and exits with code 1 when agent not published\n310: - [ ] AC011: Status retrieves AgentRuntime CR status for agentcube provider\n311: - [ ] AC012: Status retrieves Deployment status for k8s provider\n312: - [ ] AC013: Status displays results in Rich Table format\n313: - [ ] AC014: Both commands handle errors with appropriate exit codes and verbose logging\n314: \n315: ## 10. CLI Options Mapping\n316: \n317: | Command | CLI Option | Runtime Parameter | Type |\n318: |---------|------------|-------------------|------|\n319: | invoke | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n320: | invoke | `--payload` | payload | str (JSON) |\n321: | invoke | `--header` | header_list | Optional[List[str]] |\n322: | invoke | `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n323: | invoke | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n324: | status | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n325: | status | `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n326: | status | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n327: \n328: ## 11. Dependencies\n329: \n330: ### Required Runtime Dependencies\n331: \n332: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` - CLI framework\n333: - `httpx>=0.24.0` - HTTP client\n334: - `rich>=13.0.0` - Terminal formatting\n335: - `pyyaml>=6.0` - YAML parsing\n336: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` - Data validation\n337: \n338: ### Optional Dependencies\n339: \n340: - `kubernetes>=28.0.0` - K8s client (for status command)\n\n(End of file - total 340 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Command\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-023\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to deployed agents via the AgentCube Router or standard Kubernetes Service. The `status` command retrieves and displays the current status of deployed agents. Both commands work with either the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) or the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + Service).\n\n### 1.2 Package Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                              # Project metadata, dependencies\n├── agentcube/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775863982654,"end":1775863982671}}}}
